        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/place/2"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The type of innovation of this VC (Value Chain) is Endogenous and Exogenous. Commercialisation of a traditional activity, including wildlife tours designed for tourism markets, element of desination product and imagery, online bookability, bespoke &amp;apos;experiences&amp;apos; catering to visitor demand and trends for authenticity and nature. Links to remote and virtual experiences, e.g. TV programmes such as Autumn Watch, instalation of webcams, and rise of social media experience and photography sharing, stimulating demand to view species in their natutral habitat. The innovation is related to New products, New marketing strategies and other. The land use systems involved are Grassland, forestry and natural land. The local assets include Natural and cultural.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N30_VC_21_UK/event/ev11 -->


    <NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N30_VC_21_UK/event/ev11">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/event-type/valorisation_event"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/ontology#Event"/>
